author: Unity
description:
Board your ship. Fight the void. Survive together in Jump Space.
 In Jump Space, you and up to three friends crew a spaceship on daring missions across the galaxy. Seamlessly shift from piloting your vessel to spacewalking for repairs, or dropping to alien world surfaces to fight on foot — all in one fluid, high-stakes experience. Upgrade your ship, face spontaneous threats, and adapt together to conquer the unknown.

Developed by: Keepsake Games

🔗 Learn more: https://on.unity.com/jump_space 
✨ Discover more Unity-powered games: https://on.unity.com/MadeWithUnity
title: Jump Space Official Launch

author: Unity
description:
Spatial Temporal Post-Processing allows you to render your game at a lower resolution and upscale it with built-in anti-aliasing, thus significantly boosting your fps with minimal loss in visual quality. In this quick tip video, we show you how to get started using it.

Find more free Unity learn resources:
https://learn.unity.com/

#gamedev #unitytips #unity3d #unitylearn
title: Unity Tip Tuesday: Spatial Temporal Post-Processing
